        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 614 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lake Hope State Park, moving northwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nelsonville, Albany, Lake Hope State Park, Buchtel, and Zaleski.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
